		{"id":"489887a94901ec7d","type":"text","text":"[135 **HAWC (High-Altitude Water Cherenkov Observatory)** and **Fermi-LAT (Large Area Telescope)**. - Spreadsheet Google](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1lG75HDk3wCc7lvfopQ9iyqKmwniZPqGGUmJtbXLRqaQ/edit?gid=1053100296#gid=1053100296)\n    \nThe sheet appears to organize **gamma-ray source data**, likely including:\n    - Source identifiers or names\n    - Coordinates (RA/Dec)\n    - Flux or intensity measurements\n    - Event classifications (e.g., Gold/Bronze for IceCube-like events)\n    - Cross-matching between HAWC and Fermi detections\n        \n### 🎯 Purpose\n\n- To provide a **merged catalog** for analysis of astrophysical sources observed by both instruments.\n- Useful for **multi-messenger astrophysics research**, where datasets from different observatories are compared and correlated.\n\n","x":-1520,"y":-582,"width":507,"height":540},
		{"id":"f61ef4ba55bb96a9","type":"text","text":"# HAWC\n","x":-145,"y":-1360,"width":173,"height":63},
