		{"id":"ef792a86aff2d651","type":"file","file":"Anexos/canvas agns.png","x":-5160,"y":-2480,"width":2191,"height":1073,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"038e2da57adedeac","type":"file","file":"All/Others/Anexos/canvas luz de agns.md","x":-4883,"y":-1380,"width":1382,"height":880},
		{"id":"165ad5897829278c","type":"text","text":"##### [ICECAT-1: IceCube Event Catalog of Alert Tracks - Neutrino Astronomy](https://dataverse.harvard.edu/dataset.xhtml?persistentId=doi:10.7910/DVN/SCRUCD)\n\nThis catalog represents the first catalog of alerts from the IceCube Neutrino Gold and Bronze Track Alert program. Each catalog entry represents a single neutrino event potentially of astrophysical origin. This catalog includes alerts issued in realtime via GCN notices/circulars, as well as events observed in IceCube since the start of data collection with the complete IceCube detector in 2011 that would have triggered an alert had the program been in operation.|","x":-258,"y":830,"width":468,"height":380},
		{"id":"d620ced5fb27f3c2","type":"text","text":"##### [IceCat-2: Catálogo actualizado de eventos de IceCube de tracklist](https://arxiv.org/html/2507.06176v1)\n![[Pasted image 20260119113856.png]]","x":-980,"y":792,"width":566,"height":368},
